}
\value{
Plot functions return a ggplot2 object (or a patchwork object for
\code{plot_SBS288}), or NULL with a warning if the catalog is invalid (wrong
size or row names). PDF functions return NULL invisibly (called for side
effect of creating a PDF file), or stop with an error if the catalog is
invalid.
}
\description{
Plot functions for SBS, DBS, and indel mutational signature catalogs
as bar charts. Most functions return ggplot2 objects; \code{plot_SBS288}
returns a patchwork object.
}
\details{
Functions in this family:
\itemize{
\item \code{plot_SBS96}, \code{plot_SBS192}: SBS trinucleotide context
\item \code{plot_DBS78}: DBS dinucleotide substitutions
\item \code{plot_DBS144}: DBS with transcription strand
\item \code{plot_SBS12}: SBS strand bias summary (collapses 192 to 12 bars)
\item \code{plot_SBS288}: SBS with three-strand context
\item \code{plot_ID166}: Indel genic/intergenic (166 channels)
\item \code{plot_ID83}: Indel COSMIC classification (83 channels)
\item \code{plot_ID89}: Indel Koh classification (89 channels)
\item \code{plot_ID476}, \code{plot_ID476_right}: Indel with flanking context (476 channels)
}

Each has a corresponding \verb{_pdf()} variant for multi-sample PDF export.
}
